
<div class="login_info">
    <p>
This 'densha' is an example <a href="http://rubyonrails.org">Ruby On Rails&trade;</a> web application wrapping an <a href="http://openwferu.rubyforge.org">OpenWFEru</a> engine.
    </p>
    <p>
Each user of 'densha' has access to certain workitem stores and can also launch process instances.
    </p>
    <p>
<b>Warning</b> : as of now, this web application is only meant for <a href="http://getfirefox.com" title="Get Firefox !">Firefox</a> and Safari.
    </p>
    <!--p>
Log in as 'alice', 'bob' or 'admin', the password is just the username. Play around, launch processes and push workitems around.
    </p>
    <p>
There is an <a href="http://openwferu.rubyforge.org/rquickstart.html">OpenWFEru on rails quickstart</a> for local installs of this 'densha' web application.
    </p-->
</div>

<div class="login_form">
    <% form_tag do %>
        <div class="login_key">
            <label for="name">username </label>
        </div>
        <div class="login_value">
            <%= text_field_tag :name, params[:name], { :id => "tf_username" } %>
        </div>

        <div class="login_key">
            <label for="password">password </label>
        </div>
        <div class="login_value">
            <%= password_field_tag :password %>
        </div>

 		
		<div class="login_key">
            <label for="openid_url">or use your OpenID </label>
		</div>

		<div class="login_value">
            <input id="openid_url" name="openid_url" type="text" size='50' />	
		</div>

       <div class="login_key">
            &nbsp;
        </div>

	
        <div class="login_value">
            <%= submit_tag "Login" %>
        </div>
    <% end %>
</div>

<div style="clear: both;"></div>

<script>
    $('tf_username').focus();
</script>

